rows.label: qev019002_MSG0001
rows.name: What are you doing out here, human?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0002
rows.name:
...Me? I came here to mine for miranium under
orders from my employer, San'luarb.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0003
rows.name:
Though these FrontierNav data probe placement sites
continue to elude me, and the primordial creatures
are...unrelenting. Frankly, I am about at my wit's end.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0004
rows.name:
That the BLADE operatives have managed to install so
many data probes is both impressive and perplexing.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_JNK0010
rows.name: Worry

rows.label: qev019002_SEL0011
rows.name:
Suggest that Non'barac should
head back before she gets hurt.

rows.label: qev019002_JNK0020
rows.name: Query

rows.label: qev019002_SEL0021
rows.name: Ask why Non'barac doesn't just leave it to the BLADEs.

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0005
rows.name: Your concern is appreciated.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0006
rows.name:
We had aimed to establish an exclusive mineral source
with the aid of our technology, but...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0007
rows.name:
Well, I think it is quite clear that installing data
probes is no simple task.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0008
rows.name:
Under present conditions, there is a 99.87 percent
chance that I will suffer a pointless death and end up
in the digestive tract of a primordial creature.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0009
rows.name:
Quite inefficient, as I am sure you will agree.
Perhaps I will head back and propose that
San'luarb hire a human specialist in our stead.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0010
rows.name: Our technology far surpasses that of you humans.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0011
rows.name:
Given that, we believed that sourcing our own materials
would be far more efficient than relying on others.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0012
rows.name:
Yet the sensors I brought with me were of astonishingly
little use.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0013
rows.name:
It has become quite clear that we ought to rely on
your kind's expertise in this matter.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0014
rows.name:
Under present conditions, there is a 99.87 percent
chance that I will suffer a pointless death and end up
in the digestive tract of a primordial creature.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0015
rows.name:
Quite inefficient, as I am sure you will agree.
Perhaps I will head back and propose that
San'luarb hire a human specialist in our stead.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0016
rows.name:
Now, if you will excuse me? I hope we shall have a
chance to speak in a more hospitable setting some
other time.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0017
rows.name: San'luarb sent you there to assist me?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0018
rows.name:
Most appreciated. You have saved me from the near
certainty of a pointless death.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev019002_MSG0019
rows.name:
I have no miranium to show for my efforts,
but at least you have minimized our losses.[ST:wait ]
